AB  - The proceedings contain 86 papers. The topics discussed include: on the discretization of the coupled heat and electrical diffusion problems; the vector analysis grid operators for applied problems; weighted iterative operator-splitting methods and applications; a parallel algorithm for systems of convection-diffusion equations; solving coupled consolidation equations; parallel Monte Carlo sampling scheme for sphere and hemisphere; a hybrid Monte Carlo method for simulation of quantum transport; random walks for solving boundary-value problems with flux conditions; an iterative fixing variable heuristic for solving a combined blending and distribution planning problem; a hybrid metaheuristic for a real life vehicle routing problem; mixed discretization-optimization methods for nonlinear elliptic optimal control problems; and stability and bifurcation analysis of a nonlinear model of bioreactor.
